<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-462-203  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 462 203.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 27 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Romania buying California Microwave satellite systems. (Ministryof Communications may buy equipment from Satellite TransmissionsSystems subsidiary)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Satellite Transmission Systems Inc. (marketing).andO;Topic:     Romania. Ministry of CommunicationsEarth StationsNegotiation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>ROMANIA BUYING CALIFORNIA MICROWAVE SATELLITE SYSTEMS SUNNYVALE, CALIFORNIA,U.S.A., 1990 AUG 27 (NB) -- California Microwave's Satellite TransmissionSystems subsidiary is in negotiations with the Ministry of Communications ofRomania to supply a major satellite earth station to be located nearBucharest.andM;Romania is one of the first Eastern Bloc countries to be admitted to theEuropean regional satellite consortium, EuTelSat, and would be the first tocontract for EuTelSat earth station facilities.andP;  It is anticipated that theearth station would be completed in the first half of 1991, giving thegovernment of Prime Minister Iliescu direct voice, data and facsimilecommunications with all major Western European countries.andP;  The contract isexpected to be worth slightly over $3 million.andP;  Nissho Iwai of Japan willprovide financing for the project.andP;  STS is located in Hauppauge, New York.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19900824/Press Contact: Gary Gomes, STS, 516- 231-1919)</TEXT></DOC>